divs: Sighting DetailsI just discovered your organization today in an article in the Virginian Pilot newspaper. Just thought you might like to see this image while it is still on Google Streetview. I attended a funeral service at 1801 Baltic Avenue, Virginia Beach, VA yesterday, July 8th 2009. Prior to going I used Google maps to find the facility. If you spin the Streetview tool to the southeast and look over the portico you will see an interesting object. There is a Naval Air Station nearby. I flew out of there myself for many years. So there are many possibilies, but the object does not appear to be a jet, helicopter, or even a blimp. Other possibilities include a banner being towed along the beach. I ruled out a streetlight, because they can all be accounted for in the images. I can't determine the date the image was taken. Bill Miller
Summary: Unknown object caught on Google Streetview.
